title: For Sale:  7.62 Nato Israeli Military Long Range TEAR GAS Ammo - 20rds
postcontent:
This may well be the rarest 7.62x51 military ammunition ever produced anywhere - period! 

Israeli Military manufactured ammo that features a dark gray tipped bullet loaded with a Tear Gas agent.  

Based on what I was able to find - this ammo was produced in extremely limited quantities for a few months back in 1961.  

It was  designed to be able to deliver a dose of tear gas at much greater ranges than the larger caliber gas launching guns of the day were capable of (typically limited to about 150 yards). 

The idea was to shoot at a hard surface near the intended target thereby releasing the Tear Gas agent. 

I've tested several rounds of this ammo and it really works releasing a surprising amount of tear gas.

Ammo comes in it's original factory box and is in excellent (near perfect) condition.  

There are 20 rounds in the box that are loaded on four 5 round stripper clips.  

The ammo you see in the pictures is what you get. 

Primers are sealed with a purple color military sealer. 

This ammo is ever bit as deadly as any standard military ball round so it's not a novelty and must be treated with the same care as any live 7.62x51 ammunition.

title: For Sale:  8 Inch AR Pistol
postcontent:
I am looking to sell my custom built AR pistol. It is chambered in 7.62x39. I have put 100 rounds through this, just to test the reliability, and had 0 failures. 

- Anderson MFG stripped lower
- PSA Lower parts kit
- Custom bobbed hammer
- Wolff Xtra Power hammer spring
- JP Yellow lightened trigger spring
- KAK Industries Gen 2 buffer tube
- H2 Heavy buffer
- Magpul MOE+ Grip
- Magpul FDE Trigger Guard

- YHM 7.62x39 marked upper
- Ice Arms NiB coated bolt carrier
- SSA 9310 7.62x39 bolt
- DPMS charging handle
- 8 Inch MAS Defense barrel
- Guntec USA carbine free float hand guard
- Rainier Mini Comp

- ASC FDE Marlube coated mags one 10 round, one 30 round

- Primary Arms Advanced Series red dot with QD Mount

7.62x39 AR pattern rifles are notoriously hard to get functioning. I have done some simple improvements to the rifle in order to get it to feed reliably 100% of the time. 

- Custom widened and polished feed ramps on barrel and upper receiver. This ensures a perfect line up between the mating surfaces of the barrel and receiver, leaving no edges or grooves for the bullet to get caught on.
- Wolff Xtra power hammer spring. This ensures no light primer strikes on even hard mil surp ammo. This rifle was tested with Wolf and Tulammo. Both brands functioned perfectly.
- Extra power mag spring in 30 round mag. The standard mag spring was replaced with a 5% extra power standard AK mag spring. This ensures even pressure on the follower to prevent ammo from tilting in the magazine. Because of the extra length of the spring, the 30 round magazine only holds 28 rounds.
- Front edges on magazines were lowered. I did this on both the 10 and 25 round magazines. This ensures that the edge of the casing does not get caught on the edge of the magazine.

All of these simple modifications were done to ensure proper feeding and cycling of the rifle. During my testing of this rifle, I experienced 0 failures.

Looking to sell for $1000. Possible trade for semi auto hand gun + cash. Call or text REDACTED, or email me for contact.

title: For Sale:  TO ALL PRIVATE SELLERS
location: hickory, statesville, Hickory / Lenoir, North Carolina
postcontent: Some of you sellers need to read the law or at least ask your local Law Enforcement. Everybody on here says if your buying their gun, you must be ready to SURRENDER a purchase permit. Unless you hold a FFL, it is illegal for you to keep such paperwork. That paper work is to be sent to the FEDERAL Govt., not for you to keep. When selling a pistol privately, all you need is a "Signed Bill of Sale". I was in Law enforcement, and I have bought and sold several hand guns. Its ok to ask to see a purchase permit, making sure the buyer is legal, but not to keep. For me, there is way too much "personal Info" on these forms for just any Joe Blow to be keeping.

postcontent:
Very rare! Lightly used Smith and Wesson Model 19-2 in very good condition. Has cylinder and holster wear. This Smith and Wesson revolver is one of the original production 'Combat Magnum' Model 19's and is the '-4 variants produced from 1961 to early 1999 It contains all original parts and has matching serial numbers on the frame, grip, 

This Smith and Wesson Model 19-2 is chambered in .357 magnum with a 4 pinned barrel and 6 round capacity. This firearm has the original old-style rear sight leaf screw placement. This gun contains all original parts/grips 

The Model 19 was Smith and Wesson's first .357 magnum mass produced handgun, and the '-4 variant was the second variant ever produced. The Model 19 was produced in blued carbon steel or nickel-plated steel with wood or rubber combat grips, an adjustable rear sight, semi-target hammer, serrated combat-type trigger, and was available in 2.5", 4", or 6-inch barrel lengths. The Model 19 was produced from 1957 to November 1999.

title: For Sale:  Ultra Rare 1918 Mauser Tank Gewehr
postcontent: Perfect for the Military collector looking for a capstone piece. This rare piece was produced by the Germans in 1917 and 1918 due to Allied tank attacks and is credited to be the first anti-tank weapon for military use. Weighing in at 37 pounds and 5 feet 6 inches in length, the T-Gewehr was able to penetrate the armor of that period with a 13.2 X 92 MM cartridge. Has blade front and tangent rear sights, with matching numbers on the barrel, chamber, receiver, bolt components, bolt catch and barrel band, three Imperial proofs on the right side of the chamber, the Mauser banner over 1918 on the receiver ring, and a pistol grip stock. It comes with a proper reproduction swiveling riveted metal bi-pod with spiked feet. This gun is in unrestored original condition. Some light cleaning has been done to stock and barrel. The bore has been kept clean and oiled. The bolt operates smoothly and locks firmly. Patina and light rust on metal, has 2 small cracks on stock. Additional pictures can be sent on request. Serious inquiries only. This is a C+R classified gun. $7500 OBO. May consider trade for 2005 or newer mustang or dodge ram quad cab.
